It is formatted in reStructuredText and markdown . Add additional pages by creating md-files in docs and adding them to the toctree above. It is also possible to refer to the documentation of other Python packages with the Python domain syntax . By default you can reference the documentation of Sphinx , Python , NumPy , SciPy , matplotlib , Pandas , Scikit-Learn . You can add more by extending the intersphinx_mapping in your Sphinx's conf.py . The pretty useful extension autodoc is activated by default and lets you include documentation from docstrings. Docstrings can be written in Google style . {ref} genindex {ref} modindex {ref} search
